# What Spark actually is

## A distributed compute engine

- Write code as if you have **one giant table**
- Spark slices it into **partitions**, assigns each to a machine (which file + byte range to read)
- Runs your code on every partition **in parallel**, then gathers the results

## The shift from pandas

- **pandas** — one process, memory it owns directly, runs immediately
- **Spark** — a *plan* you describe, scheduled across many machines, data moved for you
- Every later idea in the course builds on this distinction
